articles.author: Monica Pitrelli
articles.title: Six travelers in Laos died from suspected methanol poisoning. Here's where incidents happen the most - CNBC
articles.description: Six travelers have died from suspected methanol poisoning in Vang Vieng, Laos. Most of these incidents occur in Asia, according to Doctors Without Borders.
articles.content:
Six travelers have died from suspected methanol poisoning after visiting the tourist town of Vang Vieng, Laos, this month.
The travelers two from Australia, two from Denmark, one from United Kingdom… [+3259 chars]
